Ab chalo EIGRP (Enhanced Interior Gateway Routing Protocol) ko detail + simple tareeke se samjh lete hain. Ye RIP se zyada advanced hai aur OSPF se simple hai.

ğŸ”¹ EIGRP (Enhanced Interior Gateway Routing Protocol)
1ï¸âƒ£ What is EIGRP?
        Developed by Cisco (pehle proprietary tha, ab open standard hai).
        Ye Advanced Distance Vector Protocol hai (kabhi ise Hybrid Protocol bhi bolte hain kyunki isme Distance Vector + Link State dono ke features hain).
        Metric = Bandwidth + Delay (not just hop count like RIP).
ğŸ‘‰ Matlab ye zyada accurate path choose karta hai compared to RIP.

2ï¸âƒ£ How EIGRP Works (Step by Step)
        Router startup â†’ Apne connected networks ko identify karta hai.
        Hello packets â†’ Neighbors dhoondhne ke liye Hello packets bhejta hai (multicast 224.0.0.10).
        Neighbor table banata hai â†’ Jis router ka reply aata hai usko neighbor maan leta hai.
        Topology table â†’ Sabhi possible routes (successors + feasible successors) yahan save hote hain.
        Routing table â†’ Best path (lowest composite metric) routing table me daal diya jata hai.
        DUAL (Diffusing Update Algorithm) â†’ Best + Backup path calculate karta hai bina loops ke.
ğŸ‘‰ RIP me loop problem hota tha, par EIGRP me nahi hota kyunki DUAL algorithm use karta hai.

3ï¸âƒ£ EIGRP Tables
        Neighbor Table â†’ Jis router se directly connected aur hello packets exchange kar rahe ho.
        Topology Table â†’ Sabhi learned routes, including backup.
        Routing Table â†’ Best routes (jo actually use honge).
4ï¸âƒ£ EIGRP Metric Formula
        EIGRP ka metric bandwidth aur delay pe based hota hai.
Formula (simplified):

        Metric=(10^7/MinBandwidth+SumDelay)âˆ—256 

ğŸ‘‰ Matlab zyada bandwidth aur kam delay wala route hamesha prefer karega.

5ï¸âƒ£ EIGRP Features
        âœ… Fast convergence (DUAL algorithm).
        âœ… Supports VLSM & CIDR.
        âœ… Load balancing (equal aur unequal cost dono).
        âœ… Sends only incremental updates (not full table like RIP).
        âœ… Supports multiple protocols (IPv4, IPv6, IPX, AppleTalk).

6ï¸âƒ£ EIGRP Packet Types
        Hello â€“ Neighbor discovery.
        Update â€“ Route info bhejna.
        Query â€“ Route info demand karna.
        Reply â€“ Query ka jawab.
        ACK â€“ Acknowledge packets.
7ï¸âƒ£ Configuration Example (Cisco)
        Router(config)# router eigrp 100
        Router(config-router)# network 192.168.1.0 0.0.0.255
        Router(config-router)# network 10.0.0.0
        Router(config-router)# no auto-summary
ğŸ‘‰ 100 = Autonomous System (AS number).
ğŸ‘‰ network = bata rahe ho kaunsa network EIGRP advertise karega.

8ï¸âƒ£ Advantages
        Better scalability than RIP.
        Loop-free (DUAL).
        Supports multiple network protocols.
        Bandwidth efficient (incremental updates).
9ï¸âƒ£ Disadvantages
        Cisco proprietary (pehle, ab thoda open hai).
        Uses more CPU & RAM than RIP.
        Not as universally supported as OSPF.
ğŸ§  One-line Memory Hooks
        EIGRP = Advanced Distance Vector (Hybrid).
        Metric = Bandwidth + Delay.
        Hello packets on 224.0.0.10.
        Tables = Neighbor, Topology, Routing.
        DUAL algorithm = loop-free + fast convergence.
        Supports unequal cost load balancing.
